    <content_encoded><![CDATA[<p>With just a few days left before the <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/06/09/brazil-world-cup_n_5475009.html">2014 World Cup in Brazil</a>, we conducted an interview with our comrades in São Paulo about the demonstrations that are unfolding. In a wave of unrest emerging on the heels of <a href="http://www.crimethinc.com/texts/recentfeatures/brazilpt1.php">last year’s riots against proposed transportation fare hikes</a>, thousands are once again <a href="http://www.aljazeera.com/news/americas/2014/05/indigenous-activists-clash-with-brazil-police-20145272348649206.html">flooding the streets and clashing with police</a> in hopes of disrupting the games. We anticipate more unrest in the coming weeks.</p>

<p><a href="http://crimethinc.com/texts/fx/worldcupbrazil.html"><strong>Read the interview.</strong></a></p>
]]></content_encoded>
