      <wp_comment_content><![CDATA[Even ABC news reporters (http://abcnews.go.com/Sports/wireStory/police-world-cup-protesters-clash-brazil-24103557) acknowledge that leadership structures just pacify movements:

"Because the recent protests have been organized by established groups, there are leaders with whom the government can negotiate. For instance, Fleischer said, in the past week the federal government convinced a large activist group of homeless workers to not demonstrate during Cup.

But there will remain remnants of protests because people who adhere to the Black Bloc movement and other "anonymous groups are difficult to negotiate with because they have no leaders to dialogue with," Fleischer said."]]></wp_comment_content>
